{"id": "session-lock-store", "phase": "store", "pillar": true, "decision": "Where does the per-session project binding live, and what keys it?", "choice": "A per-session lock at data_root()/sessions/<session_id>.json = {project, home, bound_by, ts}, keyed by session_id. Hooks already receive session_id (planaware.py:163, readtrack.py:40, autopilot.py:185), so no new plumbing. data_root() is version-independent (paths.py:26) -> the lock survives plugin version bumps, unlike the cache. BUILT+VERIFIED 2026-07-02: paths.sessions_dir/read_session_lock/write_session_lock; test_session_lock 9/9 (round-trip, session isolation, data_root location, path-injection safety). Additive -- active_project() still untouched.", "principle": "per-session-not-global", "why": "One global pointer is machine-wide mutable state decoupled from the conversation, so whatever last ran wins and concurrent sessions clobber each other. Keying by session_id gives each session its own binding.", "status": "verified", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/trainlint/tests/test_session_lock.py", "match": "sessions/|session_id|session.?lock"}
{"id": "project-home-field", "phase": "bind", "pillar": true, "decision": "What records which directory a project belongs to, so context can resolve to it?", "choice": "Add a `home` field to project.<name>.json, stamped = os.getcwd() at /trainlint:plan (and new_project.py) time, overridable. Today NO project records a home (verified: project.<name>.json has no path/cwd field) -- this is the missing context->project link. BUILT+VERIFIED 2026-07-02: paths.project_home/set_project_home (preserves other keys) + new_project.py stamps home=cwd ($TRAINLINT_PROJECT_HOME overrides) at registration; test_project_home 7/7. Backfilled this project's home -> the trainlint repo.", "principle": "context-to-project-link", "why": "You cannot resolve project-from-context if nothing maps a directory to a project. Stamping home at plan time (the one moment context is unambiguous) creates the table the resolver reads.", "status": "verified", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/trainlint/tests/test_project_home.py", "match": "project\\.[\\w-]+\\.json|\\\"home\\\"|getcwd"}
{"id": "resolution-order", "phase": "resolve", "pillar": true, "decision": "How does active_project() decide the project on any given turn?", "choice": "$HARNESS_PROJECT -> sessions/<session_id> lock -> infer (cwd or touched file paths) x each project.home by LONGEST-PREFIX, and on a hit PERSIST the session lock -> else '' (silent). No global fallback. ROLLOUT [operator-chosen 2026-07-02]: ship the new order WITH the global still as the last fallback step during migration; drop that step only in the final remove-global cut. BUILT+VERIFIED 2026-07-02: active_project() now resolves $HARNESS_PROJECT -> session lock ($CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID) -> cwd x project.home longest-prefix (persists lock) -> transitional data_root/.active-project -> ''. test_resolution 9/9; live check: THIS session resolves to session-project-lock via its /use lock. Dropped the stale legacy _PLUGIN/.active-project read.", "principle": "resolve-from-context", "why": "The resolver must prefer an explicit override, then this session's sticky lock, then derive from where you actually are; persisting on first inference makes it stable for the rest of the session instead of re-deriving every turn.", "status": "verified", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/trainlint/tests/test_resolution.py", "match": "active_project|_active\\(|HARNESS_PROJECT|resolution"}
{"id": "cwd-in-payload", "phase": "verify", "load_bearing": true, "decision": "Does the hook payload actually carry cwd (and touched file paths for PreToolUse) so per-turn context inference is even possible?", "choice": "VERIFIED YES (official docs, code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks.md, confirmed via claude-code-guide): `cwd` is a COMMON field on ALL hook events, and PreToolUse additionally carries `tool_name` + `tool_input` (so Edit/Write file_path & Bash command are available). Corroborated locally: Claude Code's own per-turn records carry top-level `cwd`+`gitBranch`. So resolution-order step 3 (infer from cwd) AND PreToolUse auto-bind from touched paths are both feasible -- the design does NOT collapse to plan-time-only.", "principle": "verify-the-frozen-interface", "why": "The infer-from-context branch (resolution-order step 3) and PreToolUse auto-bind both depend on the hook JSON providing cwd / tool paths. grep shows NO hook reads cwd today. If cwd is absent from the payload, per-turn auto-bind collapses to plan-time-explicit-bind only -- a materially smaller design. This is the cheapest test that could invalidate the plan; verify by dumping a real hook payload before building the inference path.", "status": "verified", "match": "cwd|hook.*payload|tool_input|touched"}
{"id": "switch-semantics", "phase": "switch", "decision": "How does a session change which project it's locked to?", "choice": "STICKY per session; switch ONLY on an explicit signal -- /trainlint:plan <other>, or a small new /trainlint:use <name>. NO auto-switch when cwd changes mid-session. [operator-chosen] BUILT+VERIFIED 2026-07-02: /trainlint:use (research/use.py) is the explicit switch; sticky lock + no cwd auto-switch; test_use 9/9 incl. session isolation + re-bind.", "principle": "sticky-explicit-switch", "why": "Auto-switching on every cwd/file change flip-flops and silently retargets the compass mid-work; a sticky lock with explicit switch is predictable.", "status": "verified", "match": "switch|/trainlint:use|sticky|re-?infer", "not_this": "auto-switching the locked project whenever cwd/files point elsewhere mid-session", "not_re": "auto.?switch|re-?infer.{0,20}every|switch.{0,24}on cwd", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/trainlint/tests/test_use.py"}
{"id": "remove-global", "phase": "cutover", "decision": "What happens to the old global .active-project pointer?", "choice": "REMOVE it entirely -- delete the write at new_project.py:77 and drop it from the resolution chain; NO fallback. An unbound session resolves to '' and hooks stay silent rather than narrate a stale global. [operator-chosen] ROLLOUT ORDER [operator-chosen 2026-07-02]: end state is still NO global, but during cutover KEEP .active-project as a TRANSITIONAL fallback so nothing resolves to silent; remove it LAST, only after every project has a home + /trainlint:use ships. DONE 2026-07-02: deleted the transitional global read in active_project() + both writers (new_project.py now binds the session lock instead; use.py drops the global write). A stale .active-project is now IGNORED. test_resolution/test_use updated + green; live: this session still resolves via its lock; no .active-project writer remains in code.", "principle": "no-global-mutable-state", "why": "Kept as a fallback it just reintroduces the stale-pointer bug for any unbound turn; removing it forces the honest silent-when-unbound behavior.", "status": "verified", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/trainlint/tests/test_resolution.py", "match": "\\.active-project|remove.{0,12}global|fallback", "not_this": "keeping .active-project as a last-resort fallback in the resolver", "not_re": "(fallback|last.?resort|else)[^\\n]{0,30}active.?project"}
{"id": "entry-point-rewiring", "phase": "resolve", "decision": "Given 18 call sites of _active()/active_project(), where is the session actually resolved?", "choice": "Resolve ONCE at the entry points that hold a payload/cwd -- the hooks (flow.py, planaware.py, reportcheck.py) and the CLI mains (viz/plan/deck) -- then pass the explicit name downstream (or set os.environ['HARNESS_PROJECT'] for that process). The ~18 internal name=None callers stay unchanged. BUILT 2026-07-02: NO rewiring needed -- active_project() reads $CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID + os.getcwd() directly (both present in hook AND CLI processes), so resolution stays inside paths.active_project() and all ~18 name=None callers are unchanged, exactly as decided.", "principle": "resolve-at-the-edge", "why": "Threading session_id through 18 call sites is churn; concentrating resolution at the few entry points that own the payload keeps the blast radius tiny.", "status": "verified", "match": "flow\\.py|planaware|reportcheck|active_project|entry", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/trainlint/research/paths.py"}
{"id": "migrate-existing-projects", "phase": "cutover", "decision": "How do existing projects (asr_rewrite, kimi, proposals...) get a home and stay reachable once the global is gone?", "choice": "Backfill home LAZILY -- the first /trainlint:plan or /trainlint:use on a project stamps its home; add /trainlint:use <name> to bind the current session to any existing project by name (cwd-independent). Until bound, the project is silent (not lost). PREREQUISITE to remove-global [operator-chosen 2026-07-02]: backfill EVERY existing project's home (from its known code dir) AND ship /trainlint:use BEFORE the global is dropped -- so the new resolver never leaves an old project (asr_rewrite/kimi) unresolved. BUILT 2026-07-02: /trainlint:use ships (use.py 9/9, reads $CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID so a CLI can bind); backfilled asr_rewrite home=/home/shiyil/asr/asr_rewrite. kimi/proposals are tracked fixtures, not live projects.", "principle": "lazy-backfill-no-flag-day", "why": "A hard migration of every project's home up front is a flag day; lazy backfill + an explicit /use lets old projects keep working the moment you touch them.", "status": "verified", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/trainlint/research/use.py", "match": "backfill|/trainlint:use|migrat|home"}
{"id": "reconcile-with-proposals", "phase": "store", "decision": "How does this reconcile with the existing 'proposals' bet (flat-collection: no active plan at all, many coexisting proposals)?", "choice": "COMPOSE [operator-chosen]. flat-collection owns STORAGE: N projects/proposals coexist flat with NO global active. session-project-lock owns the per-session VIEW SELECTOR: each session binds ONE of them from context. They are complementary -- both mandate killing the global .active-project; session-lock just adds 'which of the coexisting ones is THIS session focused on'. Neither supersedes the other.", "principle": "one-model-for-selection", "why": "plan.proposals.jsonl/flat-collection wants to DELETE the active concept in favor of N coexisting proposals with no privileged current one; session-project-lock keeps one-project-per-session but binds it from context. These are different selection models -- they must be reconciled (compose, or one supersedes the other) or trainlint ends up with two contradictory answers to 'which project am I on'.", "status": "decided", "match": "proposals|flat-collection|coexist|active"}
